Projects People Faculty Students About LUCI Home Welcome to LUCI The Laboratory for Ubiquitous Computing and Interaction is a research group at the University of California, Irvine that brings together faculty and students in the School of Information and Computer Science who share research interests in the design and use of ubiquitous computing platforms, infrastructures, technologies, and applications. Latest Tweets Follow us! LUCI News LUCI has a new website March 10, 2017 After a long hiatus, the Laboratory for Ubiquitous Computing and Interaction has launched a new website! Stay tuned as new content is added in the coming weeks. Kate Ringland et al. win Best Paper at ASSETS 2016 Oct 26, 2016 Congratulations to Kate Ringland et al, on their Best Paper award at Assets 2016! READ MORE LouAnne Boyd Advances to Candidacy Oct 19, 2016 Congratulations to LUCI PhD student LouAnne Boyd on her advancement to candidacy. Informatics Visit the Department Website. Useful links Department News Academic Calendar Informatics Courses Department Contact Department of Informatics Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences University of California, Irvine 5019 Donald Bren Hall Irvine, CA 92697-3440 USA Â© 2016 UC Regents